abilities and tools are designed to drive down the cost of transactions helping to meet the liquidity needs of asset managers banks brokerdealers hedge funds government agencies and public pension programs we strive to provide the most efficient execution and the highest caliber of services making markets more fair and accessible for all our team leadership peng zhao ceo peng oversees all market making activities including trading sales research and technology he previously served as head of global market making where he oversaw the firm’s global strategies across all touch points to the market direct onvenue market making retail brokerage flow and institutional client flow peng began his career with citadel securities in  as a senior quantitative researcher prior to joining the firm he worked for lehman brothers and served as a quantitative researcher for evnine  associates peng received a bachelor’s degree in applied mathematics from peking university and subsequently attended the university of california at berkeley as a berkeley fellow and graduated with a doctorate in statistics paul hamill global head of ficc paul is responsible for the clientfacing fixed income market making businesses including interest rate swaps government and corporate bonds and credit default swaps he was previously a managing director and global head of fx rates and credit execution services at ubs with responsibility for global futures execution fxpb and building the fixed income agency business which included the pin price improvement network corporate bond and cds trading platform and the neo platform for sef traded swaps paul has over  years of experience in financial services and has worked in london zurich new york and chicago with experience across ecommerce trading and sales paul has a master of arts in political science from the university of glasgow and a master of science in finance from the university of london remco lenterman head of global business development remco is responsible for driving global growth and expansion of our business across markets and into new diverse product lines prior to joining citadel securities he served as managing director at imc financial markets and was responsible for global corporate development and market structure previously he spent  years at goldman sachs as managing director responsible for pan european equity trading he also served as head of securities for five years at kempen  co remco is the chairman of the fia european principal traders association he is also currently a member of the esma consultative working group secondary markets standing committee and was formerly a member of the cftc global markets advisory committee remco received a diploma of european business administration from the european business school in london bin mu chief technology officer bin oversees the low latency strategies and research infrastructure efforts of citadel securities he previously served as head of information technology global options market making and quantitative strategies where he oversaw the development of quantitative trading systems prior to joining the firm he served as a business system analyst at first national bank he began his career as a software developer for reuters financial software bin received a bachelor’s degree from the university of science and technology of china and a master’s degree from the university of chicago nawaf bitar chief information officer nawaf leads all technologyrelated initiatives for the firm he is also a member of the board of directors of plum inc and pulse secure llc and is a venture partner at allegis capital before joining citadel securities he was senior vice president and general manager of the cloud platform business unit at vmware prior to joining vmware nawaf served as senior vice president and general manager of the security business unit at juniper networks prior to juniper he served as vice president of engineering and operations of security technology at cisco systems having joined that company in  through the acquisition of ironport systems where he was senior vice president of engineering before ironport he served as vice president of file systems and services at network appliance and previously held roles at silicon graphics apollo computer and other firms nawaf graduated from the university of texas at austin with a bachelor of arts our track record  launches electronic options market making business becoming industry leader in  months  launches options customer routing and equity market making businesses  achieves  market share in equities achieves first m contract option day  first onebillion share day in equity trading  begins delivery of algorithms to external clients  launches otc and imm market making business  launches interest rate swap market making citadel connect reaches m shares adv  launches us treasuries market making recognized as “interest rate derivatives house of the year” by risk magazine and ifr magazine wins “best electronic liquidity provider” at the markets choice awards named one of the country’s  best workplaces in financial services and insurance by great place to work  becomes  designated market maker on the nyse becomes  designated market maker on the nyse launches cdx market making wins “rates and equities flow market maker of the year” from risk magazine  also saw trading surges at critical historical moments with citadel securities managing more than a x volume increase following the us election and over x during brexit firm named one of the country’s  best workplaces for recent college graduates by great place to work firm recognized as best flow house for equities and interest rates by risk magazine global locations chicago global headquarters  south dearborn street chicago il  usa tel  fax  read more new york  park avenue between st and nd street new york ny  usa read more london  london wall london ecy et united kingdom tel  fax  read more hong kong chater house suites    c