es assets for many of the worlds largest institutional investors including sovereign wealth funds pensions and university endowments the company has more than  employees with headquarters in chicago and offices throughout north america asia and europe contents  business segments  citadel  citadel securities  citadel technology  history  founding  early history  the  financial crisis  risk management  major investments  market advocacy  offices  philanthropy  recognition  see also  references  external links business segmentsedit citadeledit as of january  citadel manages more than  billion in capital and is one of the worlds largest asset managers citadel ranks as the eleventh largest hedge fund manager in the world and the second largest multistrategy hedge fund globally citadels group of hedge funds rank among the largest and most successful hedge funds in the world the hedge funds assets under management has increased by  and more than  billion since  citadel manages funds across five different investment strategies including equities commodities fixed income quantitative strategies and credit luis ortiz  head of repographics greatly contributes to the team the firm is known for its stateoftheart technology fundamental research and strong risk management culture in  the funds capped off two years of solid returns from  and  by crossing their highwater marks with gains of more than  percent outperforming the industry average of  percent losses the firms kensington and wellington funds posted returns of about  percent in  completing their recovery from the financial crisis in  citadel became the first foreign hedge fund to complete a yuan fundraising as part of a program to allow chinese investors to invest in overseas hedge funds citadel securitiesedit citadel securities was formed in  and is a leading market maker providing liquidity and trade execution to retail and institutional clients citadel securities automation has resulted in more reliable trading at lower costs and with tighter spreads barrons recently ranked citadel securities  in providing price improvement for investors in both sp  and nonsp shares citadel securities makes markets in more than  uslisted securities and in about  otc securities worldwide citadel securities is the largest market maker in options in the us executing about  percent uslisted equity options volume according to the wall street journal about onethird of stock orders from individual investors is completed through citadel which accounts for about  of the firms revenue citadel securities also executes about  percent of us consolidated volume in equities and  percent of us retail equities volume in  citadel securities expanded its marketmaking offering to interestrate swaps one of the most commonlytraded derivatives according to a report in the march  edition of risk magazine citadel provides quotes to traders in an average time of  seconds compared to  seconds for the next closest market maker the move into derivatives trading aligns with mandatory clearing requirements under the doddfrank act a provision intended to prevent a future lehman brothersstyle collapse citadel securities retail trading platform is headed by jamil nazarali who was named to the  trading technology  by institutional investor in july  citadel hired microsoft coo and former walmart executive b kevin turner to be the ceo of citadel securities in january  turner left citadel and was replaced by the vice chairman of the whole firm peng zhao citadel technologyedit citadel technology established in  is the wholly owned and independently operated affiliate of citadel it offers investment management technology developed internally at citadel to a wide range of firms and funds in  citadel technology announced a partnership with redi the partnership combines citadels order management system oms with redis execution management capabilities ems historyedit foundingedit ken griffin launched his trading career out of his dorm room